sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: TC_032_1_CSMS: Power failure boot charging point-configured to stop transaction(s)
    Note over CP,CS: Section 3.11.1, Table 149, Page 130/176
    Note over CP,CS: Reusable State: Charging

    Note over CP,CS: [Disconnect and reconnect the power of the Charge Point.]

    CP->>CS: 1. BootNotification.req
    CS-->>CP: 2. BootNotification.conf (status = Accepted)
    Note over CS: Validation: status must be Accepted

    Note over CP: Send StatusNotification per connector and connectorId = 0

    CP->>CS: 3. StatusNotification.req (connectorId = <transaction connector>, status = Finishing)
    CS-->>CP: 4. StatusNotification.conf
    Note over CP: Validation: connector with ongoing transaction reports Finishing

    CP->>CS: 3. StatusNotification.req (connectorId = 0, status = Available)
    CS-->>CP: 4. StatusNotification.conf

    CP->>CS: 3. StatusNotification.req (other connectors, status = Available)
    CS-->>CP: 4. StatusNotification.conf
    Note over CP: Validation: all other connectors report Available

    CP->>CS: 5. StopTransaction.req (reason = PowerLoss)
    CS-->>CP: 6. StopTransaction.conf
    Note over CP: Validation: reason must be PowerLoss
